41-42. The personal reference, see Introd. p. 32, springs naturally from the similar but general contrast between past and present in the preceding distich.

42. avo: I see no reason why avus here should not be given its literal meaning, rie. the family fortune was still intact in his grandfather’s time (see Ullman, Lc. in 1, 1, 2n.).
